## How the Data Flow Works

```
┌─────────────┐    auto-save     ┌──────────────────┐
│  You edit    │ ──────────────→ │  localStorage     │
│  in browser  │                 │  (your machine)   │
└─────────────┘                  └──────────────────┘
       │                                 │
       │  click "Export"                 │
       ▼                                 │
┌─────────────────┐                      │
│  data.json      │ ← shared folder      │
│  (portable)     │                      │
└─────────────────┘                      │
       │                                 │
       │  auto-loaded on first visit     │
       ▼                                 │
┌─────────────────┐                      │
│  New browser /  │ ──── loads data.json if no localStorage exists
│  new machine    │
└─────────────────┘
```

**Key rule**: localStorage always takes priority. The `data.json` file is only auto-loaded when someone opens the app for the first time (empty localStorage). After that, they work from localStorage and re-export when ready to share.

To force a refresh from the shared `data.json`: click **Import** in the sidebar and select the file.

