## Updating the App Itself

When you want to add new seed data, change logic, or update templates:

### To update seed data (e.g. add a new RFP module)

1. Open `command-center.html` in any text editor (VS Code, Notepad++, even Notepad)
1. Find the `INITIAL_RFP_MODULES` array near the top of the `<script>` block
1. Add your new entry following the same format
1. Save the file
1. The new data appears for anyone who hasn’t already loaded data into their localStorage
1. For existing users: they can click “Reset to defaults” on that tab, or import a fresh JSON

### To update strategic templates

1. Find `STRATEGIC_TEMPLATES` in the script block
1. Edit the regex patterns or replacement text
1. Add new templates by copying the structure of an existing one

### To update the capability matrix (Sweet Spot)

1. Find `CAPABILITY_DIMENSIONS` in the script block
1. Add rows to any dimension, or change ratings from “Strong” to “Adequate” etc.
1. The heatmap regenerates automatically

### To add a new client to the Sweet Spot map

Either:

- Use the “Add Client” form in the app (persists to localStorage/export), or
- Edit `INITIAL_CLIENT_MAP` in the source for permanent default data

