## Backup Strategy

Keep it simple:

- **Weekly**: Export → save to `archive/` folder with date
- **Monthly**: Copy the entire `CommandCenter/` folder to a backup location
- Your `data.json` files ARE your backups — they’re plain text, human-readable, and contain every field from every tab

To restore from any point: click **Import** and select the archived JSON file.

-----

## Limitations to Know

|Constraint                 |Impact                                                          |Workaround                                                          |
|---------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
|localStorage is per-browser|Two people editing simultaneously won’t see each other’s changes|Agree on one “editor of record” per day, or export/import frequently|
|No real-time sync          |Not a live collaborative tool                                   |The Export/Import cycle is the sync mechanism                       |
|Browser clears localStorage|Clearing browser data wipes local edits                         |Always export before clearing cache                                 |
|SharePoint may block JS    |App might not run inline on SharePoint                          |Download and open locally, or host on a simple internal web server  |

